        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Content</head>
            <p>The collection contains eleven letters by George W. Benson, a Pennsylvania soldier stationed around Washington, D.C., Ohio, Virginia, and Pennsylvania between 1863 and 1865. The letters, written to his sister, describe camp life and his comrades. He also talks about his hopes of finding a wife when he returns home.</p>
        </scopecontent>
